headline.main: French Conservatives in Disarray as Fillon Clings On
headline.print_headline: French Conservatives in Disarray as Fillon Clings On

lead_paragraph: France's conservatives appeared to be at war with themselves less than 50 days from the presidential election as Francois Fillon clung on to his struggling, scandal-tainted campaign and senior party members fought to oust him as their candidate.
